---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="AgenticScale AI × Levenhall — Joint Press Release"
    description="AgenticScale AI has signed a partnership with Washington's Levenhall LLC to enter the US defense and national security market. Levenhall's BRIDGER and Intelligence platforms integrate into OpenScale, Agentic Shield, and Private AI."
>
    <PageHeader
        label="Joint Press Release · For Immediate Release"
        title="AgenticScale AI Picks Levenhall to Lead US Defense and National Security Expansion"
        description="Australian agentic-AI company integrates Levenhall's defense procurement and intelligence tech into OpenScale, Agentic Shield, and Private AI ahead of a US market push."
    />

    <!-- ── PARTNERSHIP BAND ── -->
    <section class="pr-band">
        <div class="container pr-band-inner">
            <img src="/images/partners/agenticscale-logo.png" alt="AgenticScale AI" class="pr-logo pr-logo-as">
            <span class="pr-x" aria-hidden="true">×</span>
            <img src="/images/levenhall-wordmark.png" alt="Levenhall" class="pr-logo pr-logo-lh">
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── RELEASE BODY ── -->
    <section class="section pr-body">
        <div class="container pr-grid">
            <article class="pr-article">
                <p class="pr-dateline"><strong>MELBOURNE &amp; WASHINGTON, DC: July 8, 2026.</strong> AgenticScale AI has signed a partnership with Washington&rsquo;s Levenhall LLC to enter the US defense and national security market.</p>

                <p>The deal puts Levenhall&rsquo;s federal procurement intelligence (<strong>BRIDGER</strong>) and geopolitical operating picture (<strong>Levenhall Intelligence</strong>) inside AgenticScale&rsquo;s enterprise AI platforms, OpenScale, Agentic Shield, and Private AI, and makes Levenhall AgenticScale&rsquo;s go-to-market partner across the Department of Defense, the Intelligence Community, defense primes, and regulated dual-use customers.</p>

                <blockquote class="pr-quote">
                    <p>&ldquo;The US defense market doesn&rsquo;t reward generalists. We needed someone who lives in it. Levenhall does. Their tech drops cleanly into ours, and they bring the relationships and the regulatory map this customer demands. We can sell into the DoD from day one because of them.&rdquo;</p>
                    <cite>&mdash; Karl Redenbach, Chief Executive Officer, AgenticScale AI</cite>
                </blockquote>

                <p>AgenticScale&rsquo;s platform is already running across finance, operations, and customer service for enterprise customers, with infrastructure partnerships through OpenAI, Microsoft, and NVIDIA. Levenhall&rsquo;s role is the defense-sector overlay: the pre-RFP procurement signal that decides federal awards, the geopolitical and country-risk picture corporate risk functions use, and the cross-border regulatory tracking (ITAR, FOCI, CFIUS, DSGL, DISP) that allied technology firms have to navigate to do business inside the US national security customer base.</p>

                <blockquote class="pr-quote">
                    <p>&ldquo;AgenticScale built the platform. Our job is to make sure the US defense customer buys it. That means the right pre-RFP signal, the right regulatory posture, and the right introductions. We&rsquo;ve done this before. We know what works.&rdquo;</p>
                    <cite>&mdash; Adam J.P. Leslie, Chief Executive Officer, Levenhall LLC</cite>
                </blockquote>

                <p class="pr-effective">The partnership is effective immediately. Initial deployments are underway with US defense and national security customers.</p>
            </article>

            <aside class="pr-aside">
                <div class="pr-panel">
                    <div class="pr-panel-head">Release / Facts</div>
                    <dl class="pr-facts">
                        <div><dt>Date</dt><dd>July 8, 2026</dd></div>
                        <div><dt>Datelines</dt><dd>Melbourne · Washington, DC</dd></div>
                        <div><dt>Levenhall Systems</dt><dd>BRIDGER · Levenhall Intelligence</dd></div>
                        <div><dt>AgenticScale Platforms</dt><dd>OpenScale · Agentic Shield · Private AI</dd></div>
                        <div><dt>Coverage</dt><dd>DoD · IC · Defense Primes · Dual-Use</dd></div>
                        <div><dt>Status</dt><dd class="gold">Effective Immediately ●</dd></div>
                    </dl>
                </div>
                <div class="pr-panel">
                    <div class="pr-panel-head">Media Contact — Levenhall</div>
                    <div class="pr-contact">
                        <span class="pr-c-name">Adam J.P. Leslie</span>
                        <span class="pr-c-role">Chief Executive Officer</span>
                        <a href="mailto:adam@levenhall.com">adam@levenhall.com</a>
                        <a href="tel:+12025682101">+1 (202) 568-2101</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </aside>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── ABOUT THE PARTIES ── -->
    <section class="section section-panel pr-about texture-grain">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">About the Parties</span>
            <div class="pr-about-grid">
                <div class="pr-about-cell">
                    <h3>About AgenticScale AI</h3>
                    <p>AgenticScale.ai is an Australian-founded enterprise AI company focused on the development and deployment of private, secure and governed AI agents for regulated industries. Operating across Australia and the United States, the company works with organisations in financial services, energy, infrastructure, government, healthcare and education to automate complex workflows, improve decision-making and accelerate operational outcomes.</p>
                    <p>AgenticScale is also the company behind <strong>Sovereign AI Infrastructure (SAII)</strong>, an asset-backed sovereign AI infrastructure program combining property, energy and NVIDIA-accelerated compute to deliver secure, sovereign AI capability across healthcare, energy, defence, government and critical infrastructure.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.agenticscale.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="mono-link">agenticscale.ai →</a>
                </div>
                <div class="pr-about-cell">
                    <h3>About Levenhall LLC</h3>
                    <p>Levenhall LLC is a Washington, DC defense and national security advisory firm. The firm serves allied technology companies, US defense primes, federal program offices, and regulated dual-use customers with US federal market entry, cross-border regulatory advisory (ITAR, FOCI, CFIUS, DSGL, DISP), executive placement, and proprietary technology products including <strong>BRIDGER</strong>, <strong>AIGIS</strong>, and <strong>Levenhall Intelligence</strong>.</p>
                    <p class="pr-ids">UEI Z4N8GQNVG826 · CAGE 20CN1</p>
                    <a href="/about" class="mono-link">About Levenhall →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <CTASection
        title="Building for the US defense market?"
        description="Schedule a confidential consultation to explore how Levenhall can support your work — whether you need market intelligence, US federal market entry, a venture engagement, or access to our products."
    />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    /* ── partnership band ── */
    .pr-band {
        background: var(--ink);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
        padding: 2.6rem 2rem;
    }

    .pr-band-inner {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: flex-start;
        gap: 2.4rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .pr-logo-as { height: 34px; width: auto; }
    .pr-logo-lh { height: 20px; width: auto; filter: brightness(0) invert(1); opacity: 0.95; }

    .pr-x {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        color: var(--gold);
    }

    /* ── release body ── */
    .pr-body { background: var(--ink); }

    .pr-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 7fr) minmax(0, 4fr);
        gap: 4rem;
    }

    .pr-article p {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 1.02rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        margin-bottom: 1.6rem;
        max-width: 62ch;
    }

    .pr-article .pr-dateline { color: var(--bone); }
    .pr-article strong { color: var(--bone); font-weight: 600; }

    .pr-quote {
        border-left: 1px solid var(--gold);
        padding: 0.4rem 0 0.4rem 1.8rem;
        margin: 2.4rem 0;
    }

    .pr-quote p {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 1.18rem;
        line-height: 1.65;
        color: var(--bone);
        margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    }

    .pr-quote cite {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-style: normal;
        font-size: 0.62rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.16em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
    }

    .pr-effective { color: var(--bone); }

    /* ── aside panels ── */
    .pr-aside {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1.4rem;
        align-self: start;
        position: sticky;
        top: 96px;
    }

    .pr-panel {
        border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
        background: var(--ink-panel);
    }

    .pr-panel-head {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 0.58rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--dim);
        padding: 0.9rem 1.2rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    }

    .pr-facts { padding: 0.4rem 1.2rem 0.9rem; }

    .pr-facts div {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 1rem;
        padding: 0.55rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft);
    }
    .pr-facts div:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

    .pr-facts dt {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 0.58rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--dim);
        flex-shrink: 0;
        padding-top: 0.15rem;
    }

    .pr-facts dd {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 0.68rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        text-align: right;
    }

    .pr-facts dd.gold { color: var(--gold); }

    .pr-contact {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.35rem;
        padding: 1rem 1.2rem 1.2rem;
    }

    .pr-c-name { font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600; color: var(--bone); font-size: 1.05rem; }
    .pr-c-role {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 0.58rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.16em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--dim);
        margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }
    .pr-contact a {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        text-decoration: none;
    }
    .pr-contact a:hover { color: var(--gold); }

    /* ── about the parties ── */
    .pr-about-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
        margin-top: 2.4rem;
    }

    .pr-about-cell { padding: 2.2rem 2.4rem; }
    .pr-about-cell + .pr-about-cell { border-left: 1px solid var(--hairline); }

    .pr-about-cell h3 {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--bone);
        margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    }

    .pr-about-cell p {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.94rem;
        line-height: 1.75;
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }

    .pr-about-cell strong { color: var(--bone); }

    .pr-ids {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 0.66rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: var(--dim);
    }

    @media (max-width: 992px) {
        .pr-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.4rem; }
        .pr-aside { position: static; }
        .pr-about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        .pr-about-cell + .pr-about-cell { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); }
    }
</style>
